Meet our newest case, Shaden. Three years ago, Shaden’s home in Syria was hit by shelling. She was just a baby at the time, and was sleeping in her cot. There was fire everywhere in her house and her mother ran into Shaden’s room and saw her tiny daughter engulfed in flames. With your donations this Christmas we can ensure we provide Shaden with the treatment she needs to smile again. Also please don't forget that every dollar is doubled - so your donations will go twice as far to helping Shaden.

THANK YOU, thank you to all who are spreading the word and helping out!
・・・
On Giving Tuesday, we smashed our own records to raise even more money for war wounded refugee children from Syria. Over the course of Giving Tuesday, one of the biggest days of philanthropy in the year, we raised $7,715. As our Christmas Appeal is currently ongoing, every single dollar was doubled to reach final figure of $15,429.36. With our average case costing $3,565, the amount raised on this day means we can help four new children in need in the new year. Thank you to everyone who posted about our work, we love you! Remember there is still a way to go to achieve our goal of raising over $150,000 for Christmas. Let's keep the momentum going! 
P.S. We also tagged just a few of the lovely people who helped raise so much money by helping lend their voices to our campaign. If we forgot you please do tag yourself! ❤️❤️❤️
